com.poesys.db.dto

Class AbstractSetter<T extends IDbDto>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.poesys.db.dto.AbstractSetter<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the kind of IDbDto processed by the setter
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ISet, java.io.Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AbstractBatchDeleteSetter, AbstractBatchInsertSetter, AbstractBatchUpdateSetter, AbstractCollectionDeleteSetter, AbstractCollectionInsertSetter, AbstractCollectionReadSetter, AbstractCollectionUpdateSetter, AbstractDeleteSetter, AbstractInsertSetter, AbstractListReadSetter, AbstractListSetter, AbstractObjectSetter, AbstractPostProcessSetter, AbstractProcessNestedObject, AbstractProcessNestedObjects, AbstractUpdateSetter

    public abstract class AbstractSetter<T extends IDbDto>
extends java.lang.Object
implements ISet
    An abstract class that centralizes things for all setters. In this version of Poesys/DB, setters use the PoesysTrackingThread to manage connections, and this abstract class implements the basic thread logic to either operate within an existing tracking thread or create a new one.
    Author:
    Robert J. Muller
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

    • Method Detail

      • set

        public void set()
        Description copied from interface: ISet

        Set a field in a Data Transfer Object (DTO). Setting a field can mean either querying data and setting it into the DTO or taking data from the DTO field and setting it into the database. The set can use batch operations, so the caller must be able to handle the BatchException as well as SQLException.

        Specified by:
        set in interface ISet
